TUESDAY MORNING ON  <http://www.cbsnews.com/sections/earlyshow/main500202.s=
html> THE EARLY SHOW

Harry Smith anchors THE EARLY SHOW from Blacksburg, VA. Russ Mitchell and M=
aggie Rodriguez, of our Miami affiliate WFOR, anchor from New York. Julie C=
hen anchors from Los Angeles. Dave Price will bring us the weather. Hannah =
Storm is off.=20

THE EARLY SHOW WILL HAVE SPECIAL COVERAGE OF "MASSACRE AT VIRGINIA TECH."=
=20

Here is a look at some of the stories we will be focusing on:=20

VIRGINIA TECH LATEST: On Monday, Virginia Tech was the scene of horrible ma=
ssacre. With at least 30 dead and close to 22 injured, it is the worst camp=
us shooting in United States history. Police say the gunman killed a victim=
 in a dorm, and then later opened fire in a classroom where most of the fat=
alities occurred. CBS News Security Correspondent Bob Orr will have the lat=
est on the gunman and what exactly happened at Virginia Tech.=20

LOU DOBBS ON SCHOOL VIOLENCE: Lou Dobbs will offer his take on school viole=
nce in his second weekly commentary.=20

HISTORY OF SCHOOL SHOOTINGS: School shootings are nothing new. In fact, bef=
ore the massacre at Virginia Tech, a shooting in 1966 was the most devastat=
ing in United States history. Now, we once again are forced to take a look =
at why such horrific violence is happening and has continued to happen for =
decades.=20

VIRGINIA TECH TRAUMA: Clinical psychologist and Early Show Contributor Robi=
n Goodman will join us to take a look at the trauma the students at Virgini=
a Tech will be experiencing. How can they begin the healing process? Also, =
we'll ask Dr. Goodman about the trauma the shooting may be causing your chi=
ldren at home. Should they watch the news with you? And is it good for them=
 to do so? We'll take a look.=20

IS YOUR CHILD SAFE?: EARLY SHOW National Correspondent Hattie Kaufman will =
take a look at campus security. Is your child safe? We'll tell you what que=
stions you need to be sure to ask on any campus tour.=20

If you would like more information on any of these stories or the broadcast=
, please click on the following address and e-mail us:=20
earlyshow@cbs.com=20

